snippet.textDisplay: The most skilled player of all time. It has been an honour watching you play. The media always disrespected your game. Always made it about MJ and Lebron but the ball players know and the millions of basketball fans know. He wasnt blessed with MJ's speed, Lebrons strength or Shaq's build. It was sheer will, his insane work ethic that carved his way to greatness. I have never seen a player carry his team the way Kobe did with his back to back championship wins without Shaq. I've never seen a player score 60 points in his final game. I've never seen a player transition from basketball player to winning an oscar for his animated short film. Another testament to his greatness. RIP Kobe Bean Bryant and his beautiful daughter Gianna.

snippet.textDisplay:
Kobe was a superhero... Watching him growing up against my Celtics were some of the most exciting times. He was the ultimate competitor and you couldn't help but dislike him on the other side, but you would always respect him. Not everyone would like Kobe because of his past and the way he would come off while he was on the court but he transitioned into an amazing influence. No one is perfect and it's how you grow as a person.


Seeing all the players that have stories about Kobe taking his time out to help them workout or critique their game, just help them anyway he can shows you what type of amazing person he was. Seeing the type of father he was, as a new father myself I strive to be like Kobe. Kobe truly was a superhero and superheroes don't leave us....That's why this is hurting everyone so much.
